  "elapsed_s": 8.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she told me [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] but I had don't want anybody from the family ever know because I don't know how they will react.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I took her down to the cellar, and she-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and she promised me that she's not going anywhere.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You know, then this resistance, the members of the resistance, they prepared for the uprising, and they cut a opening through from one cellar to another under the whole Warsaw like a honeycomb so that you did not need to move from one street to another.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You didn't need to go outside.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we are sitting in the cellar, suddenly she tells me she wants to go and see what her sister is doing just two streets away.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I told her, but you promise me you don't go anywhere else, only to sister and back.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "One hour, two hours, after three hours-- after a few hours, I don't know, we never looked in the cellar, we never watched the hours.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Somebody comes running-- family Prowyczek family Prowyczek-- because I was family, yes, and my uncle was family.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I had a funny premonition because he came from a different direction.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So I go to-- I run to him, and I ask him-- I gave my baby to somebody, I don't know who was standing there-- and I run to him.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "What happened?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So he tells me, on the way a woman started to give birth in a cellar.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they called her out-- she was a midwife-- she went, and she had to cross the street.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the first shrapnel tore her to pieces.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] So we were just waiting for a moment of silence that the German will stop shooting and we went there.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
